
[1]brigade

   BRIGA'DE, n. A party or division of troops, or soldiers,whether cavalry
   or infantry, regular or militia, commanded by a brigadier. It consists
   of an indeterminate number of regiments, squadrons, of battalions. A
   brigade of horse is a body of eight or ten squadrons; of infantry,
   four, five, or six battalions, or regiments.

   BRIGA'DE, v.t. To form into a brigade, or into brigades.
